title: Alphabet of Pop Part 16 of 26 The Letter P
description:
Well the letter P contains one or two surprises, from 50&#039;s classics by the Patters Patsy Cline you move on to 60&#039;s standards from the likes of PJ Proby and the Paper Dolls, to 70&#039;s one hit wonders Pussyfoot, the Piglets, Paper Lace and the Partridge Family.   

Watch out for one of Rod Stewart&#039;s very first records as lead singer for a group called Python Lee Jackson as well as a Guy who Annie Lennox and myself knew well as former front man for Aberdeenshire\\\&#039;s Gully Foyle, Jim Diamond and his only number one hit \\\"Don\\\&#039;t Let me Down\\\".

There is even a token Gospel record in here someplace by Parchment who made the UK top 40.   

I am on a ship at Sea so remember once I have seeded this, it is up to those who have it to keep this letter going while I move on to the lettets Q and R which will be done as one download shortly.
